I can’t press keys in your browser, but you can run this JavaScript in the page (DevTools console or a script) to simulate pressing Escape on the element with id "modal-close":

const el = document.querySelector('#modal-close');
if (el) {
  el.focus();
  ['keydown','keypress','keyup'].forEach(type => {
    const ev = new KeyboardEvent(type, {
      key: 'Escape',
      code: 'Escape',
      keyCode: 27,
      which: 27,
      bubbles: true,
      cancelable: true,
      composed: true
    });
    el.dispatchEvent(ev);
  });
} else {
  console.warn('#modal-close not found on the page.');
}

If that doesn't close the modal, some sites listen on document/window — in that case dispatch the same events on document instead of el.

I can’t press keys on your page from here, but you can simulate an Escape key press on the element with id "modal-close" using one of these snippets depending on your environment:

1) Vanilla browser JS
const el = document.querySelector('#modal-close');
if (el) {
  el.focus();
  el.dispatchEvent(new KeyboardEvent('keydown', { key: 'Escape', code: 'Escape', keyCode: 27, which: 27, bubbles: true, cancelable: true }));
  el.dispatchEvent(new KeyboardEvent('keyup',   { key: 'Escape', code: 'Escape', keyCode: 27, which: 27, bubbles: true, cancelable: true }));
}

2) Puppeteer (Node)
await page.focus('#modal-close');
await page.keyboard.press('Escape');

3) Playwright (Node)
await page.locator('#modal-close').focus();
await page.keyboard.press('Escape');
// or shorter:
await page.press('#modal-close', 'Escape');

4) Selenium (JavaScript / WebDriver)
const el = await driver.findElement(By.css('#modal-close'));
await el.sendKeys(Key.ESCAPE);

5) Selenium (Python)
el = driver.find_element(By.CSS_SELECTOR, "#modal-close")
el.send_keys(Keys.ESCAPE)

6) Cypress
cy.get('#modal-close').focus().type('{esc}')

Notes:
- The element must be focusable for some handlers to receive keyboard events; call focus() first if needed.
- If your modal listens globally (on document/window), you can dispatch the keyboard event on document or use page.keyboard.press('Escape') (Puppeteer/Playwright) without focusing a specific element.

